  "prompt": "Do all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE?",
  "response": "No, not all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE). Bluetooth 4.0 was introduced in 2010, so smartphones released before that time would not have this technology. Additionally, some budget or entry-level smartphones released after 2010 might not include Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE to keep costs down. However, most mid-range and high-end smartphones released since 2011 do have Bluetooth 4.0 or a later version, including BLE. To confirm whether a specific smartphone has Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE, you should check the device's specifications on the manufacturer's website or in the user manual.",
